<span id="freeTextContainer3811349185261446075">Now I feel a bit bad because this book came highly recommended and everyone said that this should be my first Mary Balogh. But it was a bit .... meh. It was just a bit bland and oatmealy. It was pleasant and warm but Samantha was quite annoying. She came across as very naive and a touch TSTL. So the dude you fancied when you were 18 was an idiot and broke your heart. You then refuse to go near another man for 6 years?? Seriously? And then you go on and on about finding a &quot;special companion&quot;? I j</span>
  <span id="freeText3811349185261446075" style="display:none">Now I feel a bit bad because this book came highly recommended and everyone said that this should be my first Mary Balogh. But it was a bit .... meh. It was just a bit bland and oatmealy. It was pleasant and warm but Samantha was quite annoying. She came across as very naive and a touch TSTL. So the dude you fancied when you were 18 was an idiot and broke your heart. You then refuse to go near another man for 6 years?? Seriously? And then you go on and on about finding a "special companion"? I just felt it was a bit patronising. Hartley is a man, don't offend him by being all "he will be kind and soft and gentle and blah blah blah". I'm so glad she finally got her act together in the end. But not for her sake, for Hartley's. He was the best part of the whole book. All the people around him who constantly put him down or "pitied" him can go screw themselves. I'm so glad he showed them all by punching the smugness out of Lionel!<br /><br />Don't get me wrong, the book is ok. I read this with a pleasant but somewhat slightly irritated feeling throughout. I'm gonna try some more Mary Balogh to see if her books get any better. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3811349185261446075" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

